    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1948-09-16T07:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1948-09-16T07:00:00-05:00" n="315"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d315">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">501.<gloss target="#t_BC1">BC</gloss>/9–1648:
                    Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Deputy Representative of the United States on the Security
                        Council</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Jessup</hi>
                    </persName>)<note n="1" xml:id="d315fn1">The United Nations Security Council was
                        meeting in Paris concurrently with the September opening there of the Third
                        Regular Session of the General Assembly.</note>
                    <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">confidential   urgent</hi>
                    </seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Paris</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1948-09-16T13:00:00+01:00"
                            >September 16, 1948—1 p. m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <gloss target="#t_Delga1">Delga</gloss> 52. Hyderabad Foreign Minister neglected
                    opportunity yesterday <gloss target="#t_SC1">SC</gloss> meeting to press for
                    debate and immediate vote on a cease-fire. Now he urges necessity <gloss
                        target="#t_SC1">SC</gloss> requesting immediate cease-fire in view military
                    situation without prejudice any issues involved. Cadogan, <gloss target="#t_SC1"
                        >SC</gloss> President, will call meeting tomorrow upon request any member
                    and says <gloss target="#t_UKDel1">UKDel</gloss> will vote for cease-fire
                    without prejudice any issues involved including Hyderabad’s statehood.</p>
                <p>In view Department’s 3651 to me, dated September 15, please instruct.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Jessup</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
